                    <msContents>
                        <summary>Incomplete inscription. The first of the three sections records a deed of land sale (<foreign>nila-vilai-piramāṇa-icaivu-tīṭṭu</foreign>) to Karaiyēṟaviṭṭāḷ, a <foreign>tēvaraṭiyār</foreign> of the temple who installed an image of Tiruvātavūr-nāyaṉār (Māṇikkavācakar). The endowment includes food offerings for Brahmins (<foreign>viprarici</foreign>) and for the <foreign>sandhi</foreign>.</summary> 
                    </msContents>
                    <physDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <p>No distinction between <foreign>e</foreign> and <foreign>ē</foreign>, <foreign>o</foreign> and <foreign>ō</foreign>.</p>
                        </handDesc>
                    </physDesc>
                </msDesc>
            </sourceDesc>
